<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-28T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-28T22:00:00-05:00" n="136" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d136">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/751: Telxegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ireland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dublin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-29T04:00:00+01:00">May
                                        29, 1940—4 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>27. Have cabled Kennedy warning against repercussions of steamer <hi rend="italic">Roosevelt</hi> charging same price for cots in
                                hold as for cots in public rooms, newspaper correspondents aware of
                                this injustice. Damaging <pb facs="0125" n="116" xml:id="pg_116"/>
                                scandal bound to follow, conditions at best bound to create
                                indignation. Steamer announced from America as being sent by
                                Government. No disclaimer will relieve Government of responsibility
                                in public mind. Please show President this telegram if
                                necessary.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gray</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>